    • ofBridgeImpl

      public static DummyBridgeHttpFactory ofBridgeImpl(Supplier<CycleSubscriber> cycleSubscriber, Supplier<EndpointFetcher> endpointFetcher, Supplier<BridgeHttpExecutor> pool)
      Creates a DummyBridgeHttpFactory of the actual implementation used during runtime.
      Parameters:
      cycleSubscriber - the CycleSubscriber to use for subscribing to cycle-events
      endpointFetcher - the EndpointFetcher to use to handle BridgeHttp.Endpoint requests; either networkEndpointFetcher() for the one used during runtime which actually tries to get the result from the requested url, should only be used for first tests in the beginning not for Unit-Test itself or dummyEndpointFetcher() to define dummy request handler where "static" responses can be defined, should be used for Unit-Tests
      pool - the BridgeHttpExecutor to use to handle the execution of an EndpointFetcher; either
      invalid reference 
      #asyncBridgeHttpExecutor()
      to handle the requests asynchronously or dummyBridgeHttpExecutor(Clock) to manually execute these tasks with DummyBridgeHttpExecutor.update()
      Returns:
      the created DummyBridgeHttpFactory

    • dummyBridgeHttpExecutor

      public static DummyBridgeHttpExecutor dummyBridgeHttpExecutor(Clock clock, boolean handleTasksImmediately)
      Creates a DummyBridgeHttpExecutor to handle the execution of the requests to fetch an BridgeHttp.Endpoint.
      Parameters:
      clock - the Clock to provide the current time for scheduled tasks
      handleTasksImmediately - true if all tasks which are not scheduled should be executed immediately in the same thread; false if only executed during the DummyBridgeHttpExecutor.update() method.
      Returns:
      the created DummyBridgeHttpExecutor
